{"add":{"doc":{"id":"51b77b04084dd9480ae9f4677e05137e171cf1ff9e9706a0b0520f838364ccfc","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/ba/GyorgyiNIH.jpg/220px-GyorgyiNIH.jpg","previous":[],"after":["School system","Education in Hungary is compulsory from 5 to 18 (16 for the students in grade 10 and below).[100] At the age of six, pupils enters in primary schools: the curriculum is divided in two phase of 4 years each. Afterward, they can choose between three different kind of secondary education school: Grammar school(leading to academic higher education), secondary vocational school(leading to vocational higher education) and vocational school(leading to the world of work). The system is partly flexible and bridges exist (graduates from a vocational school can achieve a two years program to have access to vocational higher education for instance).[101]"]}}}